### Analysis of CR-C and CR-A

As in Section 3.4, \(\mu_{1}>\mu_{2}\geq\ldots\geq\mu_{K}\) is assumed wlog and we further define \(\mu_{K+1}=0\). We introduce the following instance-specific quantities needed to state our error probability upper bounds. For \(j\in\{2,\ldots,K\}\), define

\[\psi_{j}=\frac{j-1}{j}\left(\mu_{1}-\frac{\sum_{k=2}^{j}\mu_{k}}{j-1}\right)^{ 2},\quad\bar{\psi}_{j}=\frac{j-1}{j}\left(\mu_{1}-\frac{\sum_{k=2}^{j-1}\mu_{ k}+\mu_{j+1}}{j-1}\right)^{2},\quad\zeta_{j}=\mu_{j}-\mu_{j+1},\]\[\varphi_{j}=\frac{\sum_{k=1}^{j}\mu_{k}}{j}-\mu_{j+1},\quad\text{and}\quad\bar{\xi }_{j}=\inf\left\{\sum_{k=1}^{K}(\lambda_{k}-\mu_{k})^{2}:\boldsymbol{\lambda} \in[0,1]^{K},\,\lambda_{1}\leq\min_{k=2,\ldots,j-1,j+1}\lambda_{k}\right\}.\]

Here we remark \(\bar{\xi}_{j}\geq\xi_{j}\) and \(\bar{\psi}_{j}\geq\psi_{j}\). These inequalities are proven in Proposition 3 and Proposition 5 in Appendix D.

**Theorem 3**.: _Let \(\boldsymbol{\mu}\in[0,1]^{K}\). Under \(\texttt{CR}-\texttt{C}\), \(\underline{\lim}_{T\to\infty}\,\frac{1}{T}\,\log\,\frac{1}{\mathbb{P}_{ \boldsymbol{\mu}}[i\neq 1]}\) is larger than_

\[2\min_{j=2,\ldots,K}\left\{\frac{\min\left\{\frac{\xi_{j}\overline{\log(j+1)(1 -\alpha_{j})\,1_{\{j\neq K\}}}}{\log j},\xi_{j}\right\},\bar{\xi}_{j}\right\}}{ j\overline{\log}K}\right\},\]

_where \(\alpha_{j}\in\mathbb{R}\) is the real number such that \(\frac{2\xi_{j}(1-\alpha_{j})}{j\overline{\log}j}=[((1+\zeta_{j})\sqrt{\alpha_ {j}}-\sqrt{\frac{1}{(j+1)\overline{\log}(j+1)}})_{+}]^{2}\)._

**Theorem 4**.: _Let \(\boldsymbol{\mu}\in[0,1]^{K}\). Under \(\texttt{CR}-\texttt{A}\), \(\underline{\lim}_{T\to\infty}\,\frac{1}{T}\,\log\,\frac{1}{\mathbb{P}_{ \boldsymbol{\mu}}[i\neq 1]}\) is larger than_

\[2\min_{j=2,\ldots,K}\left\{\frac{\min\{\underline{\max\{\frac{\underline{\psi _{j}\overline{\log}(j+1)(1-\alpha_{j})\,1_{\{j\neq K\}}}}}{\log j},\bar{\psi}_{ j}\}}{j\overline{\log}K}}{j\overline{\log}K}\right\},\]

_where \(\alpha_{j}\in\mathbb{R}\) is the real number such that \(\frac{\psi_{j}(1-\alpha_{j})}{j\overline{\log}j}=\frac{j}{j+1}[((1+\varphi_{j} )\sqrt{\alpha_{j}}-\sqrt{\frac{1}{(j+1)\overline{\log}(j+1)}})_{+}]^{2}\)._

Note that Theorem 3 implies that CR-C enjoys better performance guarantees than SR, and hence has for now the best known error probability upper bounds.

